{
  "texts": [
    "The caveat to these findings is the difference in dataset sizes, which may limit confidence in the meaning found in direct comparisons.",
    "More comparable results might be obtained if the datasets were of similar size (according to [43]).In terms of practical use, CR, CR-POS and NDS ran quickly.",
    "However, HS is quite slow and not recommended for larger datasets.",
    "Even for the smaller datasets in this study, HS was quite slow on a basic desktop, taking 41 minutes for the Word+Review dataset, 1 hour 40 minutes for the Review+Word dataset, and 4 hours 43 minutes for the Supply-Word dataset.TABLE IV COMPARISON OF TARGET AND EVALUATED SCORES Word+Review Review+Word Supply-Word-Mini Supply-Word-4o Expected Generated Expected Generated Expected Generated Expected Generated Mean 0.51 0.58 0.50 0.53 0.65 0.74 0.65 0.74 Variance 0.09 0.13 0.09 0.13 0.08 0.09 0.08 0.09 MAD 0.13 0.09 0.10 0.09 MSD 0.02 0.01 0.01 0.01 Pearson 0.93 0.96 0.97 0.98 tStat -16.43 -8.14 -43.00 -45.90 TABLE V TEXT DIVERSITY SCORING FOR THE THREE PDT DATASETS Method CR CR-POS HS NDS Words Word+Review 4.397 6.715 0.208 1.559 49,131 Review+Word 4.727 6.871 0.234 1.323 76,107 Supply-Word 3.729 6.179 0.200 1.650 128,115 D. PDT Dataset Costs (RQ4)Table VI shows the costs of data generation in terms of time, tokens and gpt-4o-mini price per method.",
    "At the time of running the experiments in Oct 2024, gpt-4o-mini dollar costs were relatively low at $0.15/1M input tokens and $0.60/1M output tokens [45], making it more ideal for big data synthesis tasks compared to some of the other massive commercial LLMs."
